snippet.textDisplay: Love Dyson but I can't justify  spending that much on a straightener. Technique wise, heat protectant, brush each section gently, use smaller sections (this eliminates the need to make multiple passes), use a fine tooth comb and follow directly with the straightener (the sections were a bit tangled), and don't do so many passes on one section. Must prevent heat and styling damage! Hope this helps! ☺️
